# Third-Party Licenses

This document contains the licenses for all third-party Rust crates compiled
into the **MAKI** binary. It is generated automatically by [`cargo-about`]
and shipped alongside each release.

MAKI itself is released under the Apache-2.0 license. The Rust crates listed
below are used under the terms of their respective licenses, all of which are
permissive open-source licenses (MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD, ISC, MPL-2.0, etc.).

For external tools like `dcraw`, `libraw`, `ffmpeg`, and `curl`, MAKI only
calls them as separate processes and does not bundle their code; they are
governed by their own licenses and installed separately by the user.

For AI models (SigLIP, SigLIP 2, face detection/recognition), MAKI downloads
weights on demand from Hugging Face. Those models are released by Google and
the Hugging Face community under Apache-2.0; MAKI does not bundle them in
the binary.

[`cargo-about`]: https://github.com/EmbarkStudios/cargo-about

